The paper discusses cryptographic protocols and their analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of model-finders and SMT technology suggests a focus on logic and automated reasoning (cs.LO), while the use of scripting and algorithms suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The discussion of homomorphism and embedding preorders suggests a focus on algebra and category theory, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of two cooperating programs and the discussion of protocol execution models suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
